    <tags>oqtane module form builder survey payment</tags>
    <releaseNotes>v1.7.77 (20260705) — ✨ NEW per-preset editable colour palette in the ⚙ Settings → Theme &amp; Layout → Theme preset section. Each preset tile now has a ▾ caret that drops down an editable palette of the four semantic colours it is built from — Primary, Text, Surface, Accent — each with a native colour picker AND a typed hex field (kept in sync). Editing a colour re-applies the full --mf-* palette to the form, selects that preset, and marks it dirty; the Save button persists it (module style) and the render consumes it. A "Reset to default" restores the preset's shipped colours. Verified end-to-end: edit Ocean Primary → #e11d48 → Save → submit button renders rgb(225,29,72) → reopen shows the edited hex. AssetVersion→20260705-B366. Carries v1.7.76.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.76 (20260705) — 🔧 FIX Theme &amp; Layout settings (Field spacing / preset / max-width) appeared to never save — the ⚙ settings popup's slider always showed the 20px default on reopen and admins thought nothing persisted. Root cause: GET ModuleConfig/ModuleStyle returned a raw Newtonsoft JObject, but Oqtane serializes controller responses with System.Text.Json, which cannot serialize a Newtonsoft JObject and emitted garbage (themeCssOverrides → [[[]]]) — so the client read every var as unset and the slider fell back to its default. The save DID persist (DB correct) and the public render DID apply the value (verified: 15px stored → 15px actual field gap); only the popup's read-back was broken. GetModuleStyle now returns a System.Text.Json JsonElement (both the stored and seed-from-form paths). Oqtane-only (Web/DNN use Newtonsoft output). Server-DLL-only fix; AssetVersion unchanged (B365). Carries v1.7.75.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.75 (20260705) — 🔧 FIX SEC-B1 regression: adding [ValidateAntiForgeryToken] to Oqtane SaveModuleStyle in v1.7.74 made the module-style Save return 400 when the ⚙ settings popup opened on a page that loads ONLY megaform-settings-popup.js (a rendered form in edit mode) — that bundle did not install the same-origin antiforgery header chokepoint, so its fetch never carried X-XSRF-TOKEN-HEADER. The settings-popup entry now imports shared/antiforgery so the chokepoint self-installs and SaveStyle/SaveModuleStyle carry the token. AssetVersion→20260705-B365 (busts the cached settings-popup bundle). Carries v1.7.74.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.74 (20260705) — 🔒 SECURITY + ⚡ PERF (Sprint 0+1 remediation, commit e589ab6). SECURITY: (SEC-B1) Oqtane SaveModuleStyle now carries [ValidateAntiForgeryToken] (was CSRF-exposed under the class-level [IgnoreAntiforgeryToken]; client already sends the token via the shared antiforgery chokepoint). (SEC-B2) payment amount enforcement was effectively a NO-OP because the unified payment widget never sent formId, so the server always fail-opened to the client "amount" — the widget now stamps data-mf-form-id and sends it in the Stripe/PayPal create bodies, and PaymentController.ResolveServerAmount now FAILS CLOSED when the form context is missing (deploy the plugin + server together; a stale plugin omits formId and is rejected). (SEC-M) WebhookService now routes user-configured webhook URLs through SsrfGuard (previously only the workflow WebhookNodeExecutor did). PERF: (PERF-A1) content-addressed memoization of RenderModelResolver.ResolveSchemaJson — the heaviest render step (JObject parse + DeepClone + ToString of ~165 KB schemas, run 5-6x per public form view) — plus a 30s TTL cache for the per-render license.lic disk read; (PERF-C1) DNN RazorWidget proxy uses one shared HttpClient + per-call CancellationTokenSource instead of 6 per-call clients (socket exhaustion); (PERF-C2) captcha verification uses a shared static HttpClient with a 10s timeout on the public submit path; (OPS-1) per-IP flood rate limiter on the standalone Web host. AssetVersion→20260705-B364 (payment plugin recompiled). Carries v1.7.73.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.73 (20260704) — 🔒 SECURITY (2 more flow-safe hardenings from the Mythos re-audit) + AssetVersion→20260704-B363. (P1-2/P1-11) The Oqtane module style / ModuleConfig / image-upload popup endpoints (SaveStyle, SaveModuleStyle, GetModuleStyle, GetModuleConfig, SaveModuleConfig, Upload/Image, Upload/List) gated on CanUseAdminPopup() which only checked IsAuthenticated — so ANY logged-in user (incl. a low-privilege registered user) could POST an arbitrary victim's moduleId (a cross-module IDOR whose SaveModuleStyle write is also a stored-XSS vector). CanUseAdminPopup now requires the site Admin or Host role. (Deliberately NOT the stricter per-target-module EditModule policy: the cross-platform settings popup often calls these WITHOUT the alias prefix so AuthEntityId can't resolve the module — an EditModule/AuthEntityId check would 403 that legitimate path; role-gating closes the "any authenticated user" hole without breaking it. Per-module ownership remains a follow-up.) (P2-8) The builder inline-edit preview posted the form's full schema/settings to window.parent using a target origin derived from document.referrer, which a page that cross-embeds the builder preview could poison to receive it — now always posts to the same-origin parent (never document.referrer), and the builder receiver validates event.origin === location.origin. Server + JS bundles (megaform-renderer.js + megaform-builder.js) rebuilt. Carries v1.7.72.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.72 (20260703) — 🔒 SECURITY (P1/P2/P3 flow-safe pass) + field-spacing cache-bust + AssetVersion→20260703-B360. SECURITY (surgical, form build/render/submit/payment flows unaffected — see Docs/SECURITY_P1_P2_P3_REMEDIATION_2026-07-03.md): (P0-8, NEW) Workflow Webhook SSRF — a PUBLIC form submission could steer the server's outbound webhook at cloud metadata / internal hosts via {{field.*}} URL tokens; new MegaForm.Core SsrfGuard rejects non-http(s) + loopback/private/link-local/CGNAT/metadata (169.254.169.254) targets (DNS resolved up-front so rebinding is caught), with an on-prem opt-out env MEGAFORM_ALLOW_PRIVATE_WEBHOOKS=1. (P0-9, NEW) MegaForm.AspNetCore.Component hardcoded JWT key + disabled issuer/audience validation → now env-first (MEGAFORM_JWT_KEY) and validates issuer/audience when configured, mirroring the Web host. (P1-3) Web Local-AI kimi CLI spawn restricted to Admin/Host (KB answers stay open to any authed user). (P1-4/5/6) the option-source / DatabaseInsert / lifecycle-hook SQL guards (all run on public-facing paths) were substring-matched ("INSERT " with a trailing space) — hardened to word-boundary + reject statement-stacking + reject comment obfuscation, so INSERT\tINTO / "…;UPDATE…" bypasses are closed while single legit statements still run; stored-proc option names restricted to a plain identifier. (P1-8) Files/Download path traversal — replaced the bypassable path.Replace("..","") with canonical Path.GetFullPath containment (Oqtane + DNN). (P2-1) CORS lockable to MEGAFORM_CORS_ORIGINS (Web + AspNetCore.Component); (P2-2) Component auth cookie Secure outside Development; (P2-4) X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff on private downloads. DEFERRED (would break the workflow, documented not applied): P0-1 unauth RazorWidget DML + P0-2 payment amount (need server-side schema/price resolution), P1-1/P1-2 class-level antiforgery removal (needs the JS fetch layer to send a token first), P1-7 content-token SSR encoding (premium templates embed HTML in tokens), P3 config defaults (flipping TrustServerCertificate breaks local SQL). FIELD-SPACING: the v1.7.71 rebuilt megaform-settings-popup.js bundle now cache-busts for all browsers (AssetVersion bumped B359→B360) so the "Field spacing" slider reflects the saved --mf-field-gap without a manual hard-refresh. Carries v1.7.71/70/69/68.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.71 (20260703) — FIX Settings → "Field spacing" slider appeared to not save (always reverted to 20px). The value DID persist and DID apply to the rendered form (MegaForm:ModuleStyleJson stored --mf-field-gap and the render emitted it) — but the module's megaform-settings-popup.js bundle in wwwroot was STALE (never rebuilt by `npm run build`, which omits the settings-popup entry), so the deployed slider re-read the wrong source on reopen and showed the 20px default. Rebuilt megaform-settings-popup.js from current source (loadFormTheme awaits getModuleStyle — the module-owned style — before building the slider) so the slider now reflects the saved value. No C# change; carries the v1.7.70 Rating fix + v1.7.69 security + v1.7.68 KB eager-seed. (NOTE for maintainers: add build:settings-popup to the npm `build` script so this bundle stops going stale.)
      PREVIOUS v1.7.70 (20260703) — FIX Rating widget rendered VERTICALLY on server-rendered forms. FormHtmlRenderer emitted the star spans (&lt;span class="mf-star"&gt;) as DIRECT children of .mf-rating, which is display:grid — so each star fell on its own grid row (stars stacked top-to-bottom). The client renderer (inputs.ts) wraps them in the flex .mf-rating-items; the SSR path did not — an SSR/client parity gap. FormHtmlRenderer now emits the same structure (.mf-rating--star &gt; .mf-rating-items &gt; button.mf-rating-item.mf-star with .mf-rating-on/off), so the stars lay out horizontally and hydrate/style consistently. Added a defensive CSS net (.mf-rating:has(&gt; .mf-star)) for any legacy bare-star markup. Server-DLL fix; note: the module Settings pane already exposes vertical row spacing as "Field spacing" (var --mf-field-gap) under Theme &amp; Layout. Carries v1.7.69 security. Carries v1.7.68 KB eager-seed.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.69 (20260703) — 🔒 SECURITY (P0 remediation, flow-safe). Fixes for the Mythos audit's Critical findings, made surgically so the form build/render/submit/payment flows are unaffected: (P0-1) the Razor-widget Action SQL path (EditableList/MasterDetailList) now runs client SQL through a new destructive-SQL guard (MegaForm.Core RazorActionSqlGuard) — SELECT/INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE still pass so the widget Add/Edit/Delete buttons keep working, but DROP/ALTER/EXEC/xp_/sp_/statement-stacking/comments are rejected, closing the unauthenticated "DROP TABLE" hole. (P0-4) the Oqtane Local-AI chat/completions endpoint (builder assistant, can spawn the env-gated kimi CLI) is tightened from any-authenticated-user to Admin/Host only. (P0-3) the Web Local-AI chat/completions endpoint drops [AllowAnonymous] → [Authorize]. (P0-6) ModuleCssComposer now neutralises the "&lt;/" token in authored customCss/moduleCssOverride so a payload can't break out of the &lt;style&gt; block (stored XSS); raw CustomHtml is intentionally left as-is (admin-authored premium-shell feature). (P0-7, DNN) the public AppEndpoint SQL guard now rejects any DML/DDL keyword anywhere (word-boundary), closing the "WITH cte … DELETE" CTE-hidden-write bypass. (P0-5, Web) the JWT signing key + issuer/audience are read from environment variables first and the committed production key was rotated to a placeholder (set MEGAFORM_JWT_KEY on the host). (P0-2) payment amount tampering is documented in-code as needing a coordinated widget+schema change (server-side price resolution) and is NOT auto-fixed, to avoid breaking variable-amount forms. Server/Core/Web/DNN all compile clean. Carries v1.7.68.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.68 (20260703) — ⭐FIX empty AI Knowledge Base on fresh NuGet installs (MF_AI_Knowledge = 0 rows → AI premium-edit had no KB context). Root cause was NOT the migration seed SQL: on Oqtane MegaFormManager.Install() builds the schema from the EF MODEL (GenerateCreateScript) and SeedMigrationHistory() marks EVERY migration applied WITHOUT ever running its Up() — so the template-guide seed in migrations 01.06.35/36/37 is dead code here and never executed. The only runtime seed path is the LAZY JSON seeder (OqtaneKbSeederHostedService.SeedEntries, embedded ai-knowledge-seed.json) which fires on the first authenticated KB read — so a fresh install with no AI use sits at 0 rows. Fix: (1) MegaFormManager.Install now EAGERLY seeds the KB (entries + templates + rules) right after creating the schema, in the install request scope where the tenant connection is resolved — idempotent (empty-check) and defensive (a seed hiccup never fails the module install; the lazy first-read seed remains as fallback). (2) Added the 3 recent premium template_guide entries (americana-journey, event-registration-rsvp, wellness-patient-intake) that migration 37 introduced but that never seeded on Oqtane (their Up() is dead code) so the AI premium-edit assistant gets their .guide.md design context — the JSON now seeds 321 KB rows (24→27 template_guides; the other premium templates already ship as form_template entries and can't hold a second row per slug). Removed the useless migration 01.06.38 (Up() never runs on Oqtane). Verified on the clean SQL Express :5100 site: MF_AI_Knowledge goes 0 → 321 on upgrade. Server-DLL-only change (no wwwroot/JS churn); AssetVersion unchanged. Carries v1.7.66.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.66 (20260703) — Two Blazor enhanced-nav (SPA) fixes: (1) Builder rendered BLANK when navigating in-tab to a different builder (?mfpanel=builder&amp;formId=N) — the loader guard was a GLOBAL flag that stuck true across SPA nav; now per-root (root.dataset.mfBooted) + MegaFormBuilder.reInit wired to re-boot a freshly-mounted empty root. (2) Two forms overlapped when switching forms in-tab — the renderer now drops any stale sibling .mf-form-wrapper in the module container before render (1 module = 1 form). AssetVersion→20260703-B359. &#10;PREVIOUS v1.7.65 (20260703) — Builder boot: dedupe the duplicate Form/Get. The builder has two boot paths (panels.ts initBuilder + dom.ts bootBuilderDom) that BOTH fetched the same Form/Get on open — on a real form that is 2× ~3s identical requests. A shared in-flight promise cache (boot-fetch-dedup.ts) keyed by formId now serves one request to both paths, cutting ~3s off builder open. Perf note: the remaining builder slowness is HTTP/1.1 connection queueing (118 resources) — needs HTTP/2 (requires TLS) — plus eager widget-plugin registration (~2.4MB JS) that should lazy-load on drag; these are follow-ups. AssetVersion→20260703-B358.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.64 (20260703) — Premium template-guide KB seed completeness: added the AI premium-edit KB seed rows for americana-journey + the two new templates event-registration-rsvp and wellness-patient-intake (their .facts.json/.guide.md already shipped, but no MF_AI_Knowledge row existed, so the AI assistant lacked per-template context). Added to the canonical Seed/ai-knowledge-template-guides.sql + a new idempotent migration 01.06.37 (MERGE / INSERT-WHERE-NOT-EXISTS, safe on existing DBs). Package now passes verify-package-complete for all 7 shipped premium templates. Carries the dashboard FOUC fix + 2 new templates + first-paint anti-jank work.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.63 (20260703) — Dashboard FOUC fix: the admin/dashboard shell CSS (megaform-admin-shell.css) was only delivered via the async JS boot &lt;link&gt;, which on the Interactive host is eval'd ~2.5s into boot — so ?mfpanel=dashboard painted UNSTYLED then snapped into place (flicker). It is now emitted as a render-blocking &lt;link&gt; inside the prerendered panel markup so the browser has the shell CSS before the dashboard paints; the JS boot still re-injects it for SPA panel nav (idempotent). AssetVersion→20260703-B357. Carries the two new premium templates + first-paint anti-jank work.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.62 (20260703) — Two new premium templates shipped: "Event Registration &amp; RSVP" (event-registration-rsvp) and "Wellness &amp; Patient Intake" (wellness-patient-intake) added to wwwroot/Modules/MegaForm/Templates so a clean NuGet install seeds them into the gallery like the other premium starters. Fixed an invalid `type:"Input"` on their name/text fields → `Text` (Input is not a recognized MegaForm field type, so those fields fell through to the default renderer). Carries the v1.7.60/61 first-paint anti-jank work (auFade cloak + premium-native multistep gap:0).
      PREVIOUS v1.7.61 (20260703) — Premium-native top-gap jump fix: the generic multi-step shell the renderer wraps around a custom form is `display:flex;gap:20px` between its header/body/footer. Premium shells (australia/americana/…) render their OWN stepper + Back/Next/Submit so that header/footer are hidden, but the flex gap still reserved ~20px above AND below the card — and because the shell is built by JS AFTER the SSR card has painted, those 40px land LATE, dropping the card ~20px and growing the block ~40px = a visible top-padding "giật". An americana-only rule already zeroed this; now a general `.mf-premium-native-mode.mf-has-multistep-shell .mf-multistep-frame{gap:0}` covers every premium template (down-under included). AssetVersion→20260703-B356. Carries v1.7.60.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.60 (20260702) — First-paint anti-jank cloak (SSR-baked, no re-trigger): the real cause of the premium-form "giật" is the per-step entrance keyframe (auFade/amFade: opacity 0→1 + translateY 6px) which — because .au-page.is-active + the animation live in the SSR template CSS — PLAYS AT SERVER FIRST PAINT (~250ms), before the schema returns. v1.7.59 cloaked only after JS ran (too late) and used animation:none, which restarted the entrance the moment the class lifted. Now the SSR wrapper ships with .mf-booting baked in (Index.razor + /render), .mf-booting pushes one-shot entrances to their final frame via a large negative animation-delay (no motion, no 0%-flash, animation-name stays detectable), and the renderer PINS the on-screen step's entrance off before lifting the class one frame after hydrate — so it never replays. Step-change animations during real navigation are untouched; spinners keep spinning. AssetVersion→20260702-B355. Carries v1.7.58.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.59 (20260702) — First-paint anti-jank cloak: on Oqtane Interactive the schema is fetched ~250ms after first paint, so the renderer hydrates the form late and premium shells run their per-step entrance animation (auFade/amFade: opacity 0→1 + translateY(6px)) plus a width settle transition AFTER the page has painted — reading as a visible fade+slide "giật", not an effect. The renderer now cloaks the wrapper with .mf-booting (animation:none + transition:none) around the whole synchronous hydrate and lifts it on the next frame, so the first step lands in its final position instantly while real step-change animations still play during navigation. AssetVersion→20260702-B354. Carries v1.7.58.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.58 (20260702) — Custom-shell SSR bind-only completion: the public renderer now detects data-mf-ssr customHtml shells and hydrates bind-only (conditional logic, managed scripts, native Back/Next/Submit) instead of calling renderCustomHtml()/innerHTML after paint. Combined with v1.7.57 Row de-dup, this prevents both the 4-column→2-column snap and the later custom shell repaint on FormId 4. AssetVersion→20260702-B353. Carries v1.7.57.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.57 (20260702) — Row SSR first-paint parity: FormHtmlRenderer collapses exact duplicate Row columns caused by legacy payloads carrying both columns and Columns, so first/last name paints as 2 columns from SSR instead of snapping back after JS hydrate. Carries v1.7.56.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.56 (20260702) — Custom-shell header first-paint parity: FormHtmlRenderer now receives the persisted form title/description/submit text from Oqtane host and /render, so {{form:title}} and {{form:description}} are filled in SSR instead of appearing later when JS hydrates. Prevents header-on forms from pushing fields down after paint. AssetVersion→20260702-B352. Carries v1.7.55.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.55 (20260702) — Custom-shell Hide Form Header first-paint coverage: core megaform.css now also collapses mfp-card-header/default/header/title/desc selectors under mf-hide-header, so Custom HTML Active forms do not show the template header/title during first paint. AssetVersion→20260702-B351. Carries v1.7.54.
      PREVIOUS v1.7.54 (20260702) — Hide Form Header first-paint fix: when settings.hideHeader is true, Oqtane SSR and /api/MegaForm/render no longer emit the standard form header/title markup, renderer fallback skips header creation too, and megaform.css carries an early mf-hide-header collapse rule. Prevents late header/title appearance from shifting the form after paint. AssetVersion→20260702-B350. Carries v1.7.53.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.53 (20260702) — Oqtane Interactive one-pass SSR hydration: renderer skips duplicate init once SSR DOM is hydrated, full SSR shells bypass buildSkeleton entirely, and the Oqtane boot script locks per container/form before schema fetch so the form prepares once and then only JS-binds navigation/validation/submit. AssetVersion→20260702-B349. Carries v1.7.52.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.52 (20260702) — Deploy-correct hidden-root keepalive: synced the Oqtane packaged wwwroot megaform.css source with the direct-body display:none keepalive rule, so the package actually ships the black/blank-frame fix. AssetVersion→20260702-B348. Carries v1.7.51.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.51 (20260702) — Oqtane Interactive hidden-root keepalive: megaform.css now force-displays the direct body prerender wrapper only when it contains MegaForm SSR, preventing Oqtane's temporary display:none boot wrapper from producing a black/blank frame before the live tree appears. AssetVersion→20260702-B347. Carries v1.7.50.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.50 (20260702) — SSR snapshot restore hardening: stores first-paint form HTML under exact module key plus site/form and form-only fallback keys, so the Oqtane Interactive circuit can restore _ssrFieldsHtml during its loading pass even when PageId/ModuleId state differs from prerender. Closes the remaining post-negotiate blank window before bind-only hydration. AssetVersion→20260702-B346. Carries v1.7.49.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.49 (20260702) — SSR multi-step anti-blank guard for Oqtane Interactive: suppresses the transient loading render while the interactive circuit is rebuilding SSR state, preserving the prerendered server form DOM until _ssrFieldsHtml is ready. Prevents the short black/blank swap seen between SSR markup and final hydrated form. AssetVersion→20260702-B345. Carries v1.7.48.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.48 (20260702) — SSR multi-step first paint: standard multi-step forms now render server-side with .mf-page wrappers, stepper, actions, and a full Oqtane shell so the Interactive host does not tear SSR into a skeleton while waiting for the Blazor circuit. Renderer detects data-mf-ssr-multistep and hydrates bind-only instead of rebuilding pages/stepper. AssetVersion→20260702-B344. Carries v1.7.47.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.47 (20260702) — 🔒 SECURITY (unauth remediation) + FOUC root-cause fix. (1) P0-1 kimi local-AI RCE (Oqtane MegaFormLocalAiController): the /api/MegaFormAi/chat/completions fallback shelled out to a local `kimi` CLI with the user query STRING-INTERPOLATED into the args and NO env gate → unauth argument injection / RCE. Now: [Authorize] on the endpoint + opt-in env gate MEGAFORM_ALLOW_LOCAL_AI_CLI=1 + ProcessStartInfo.ArgumentList (argv array, no shell string) — mirrors the already-safe Web variant. (2) P0-2 i18n write→stored-XSS (Oqtane MegaFormController.UpsertI18nLocale, routes i18n/create·save·import): was the only write path in the controller WITHOUT [Authorize] → anyone could write attacker JSON to a locale file rendered in the builder. Added [Authorize(Policy=EditModule)] + reject overwriting the `index` manifest. (3) P0-5 SavePrintSettings (Web PrintController): unauthenticated → anyone could rewrite a form's print header/footer HTML (stored XSS). Added [Authorize(Roles=Administrator)]. (4) AiKnowledgeController.SeedViewModes: was the lone KB mutator missing the `if(!IsAdmin) return Forbid();` guard → anon DB write; added it. (5) ⭐FOUC/double-render fix: FormHtmlRenderer.RenderFieldsBody now de-dupes fields by key before SSR (matching the client's byKey hydrate). A form whose stored schema had every field duplicated painted 36 field-groups for 18 fields → a visible "double-then-collapse" flash + 2x payload. NOTE: two unauthenticated surfaces remain FLAGGED for a design fix (server-side validation, not a bare [Authorize]): RazorWidget/Action (arbitrary SQL, but invoked by anonymous form runtime) and PaymentController stripe/paypal (merchant-credential endpoints legitimately hit by anonymous payers). AssetVersion unchanged (server-only). Carries v1.7.46.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.46 (20260702) — (1) FIX duplicate footer buttons on premium-native shells (euro-youth/intake/down-under/festa/bulgaria): the shell renders its own Back/Next/Submit AND the generic renderer injected .mf-form-actions → two "Next"/"Submit" buttons. Now hidden deterministically from first paint via CSS keyed on the always-set .mf-premium-native-mode wrapper class (also removes the generic-actions flash). (2) Inspector colour rows get a curated COLOUR PALETTE popover (swatch grid + recent + native custom picker) instead of just the OS picker. AssetVersion→20260702-B343. Carries v1.7.45.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.45 (20260702) — Theme Designer (builder Design tab): (1) removed the unfinished/unused LEFT-rail Elements + Colors tabs (only Presets remains). (2) Typography font dropdowns now have a clearly visible border + chevron (was near-invisible #e2e8f0 and could be overridden by the host Bootstrap .form-control). (3) The CSS element picker moved from the (removed) left Colors tab to the RIGHT-rail Inspector sub-tab and was FIXED to actually work: it silently did nothing because (a) the pick-result event was dispatched non-bubbling on document but the panel listens on window, and (b) the iframe applied edits as plain inline style which premium template CSS (!important) overrode. Now: Pick element → the picked element's CSS lists on the right with per-property inputs + colour swatches, and edits apply live to the preview (inline !important). AssetVersion→20260702-B342. Carries all v1.7.44 fixes.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.40 (20260701) — ⭐CRITICAL DEPLOY FIX: the Oqtane ModuleDefinition.Version was frozen at "1.7.15" across every release, so Oqtane treated each new package as "already installed" and NEVER replaced the module DLLs on upgrade (only wwwroot updated) — every C# fix since 1.7.15 silently failed to deploy on existing sites. Bumped ModuleDefinition.Version to 1.7.40 (+ ReleaseVersions) so upgrades actually swap the DLLs. This finally deploys the v1.7.38 i18n Save fix + v1.7.39 template-seed and dashboard bloat-guard on upgraded sites. (1) FIX empty Business Starters / Template Gallery on a CLEAN install: the premium starter templates were only read from App_Data/MegaForm/Templates, which the NuGet never populated → BuilderTemplateCatalogService now SEEDS App_Data from the shipped wwwroot/Modules/MegaForm/Templates copy on first run (5 premium templates now ship in the package). (2) FIX "Dashboard shows no forms" on a fresh site: an AI form with a QRCode field holding a 1.5MB base64 logo produced a 3MB schema; rendering it inline as a Blazor MarkupString threw "Unexpected end of input" in insertMarkup and ABORTED the whole page render, so the dashboard's form-list load never ran. Added a ~700KB size guard on the inline schema preload + SSR fields body — oversized forms fall back to the client fetch/render instead of crashing. Carries v1.7.38 i18n Save fix.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.38 (20260701) — ⭐FIX Language Manager "Save" not persisting: the i18n Get endpoint read js/bundles/i18n (shipped defaults) BEFORE js/builder/i18n (author overrides written by i18n/save). Since the package ships every locale in bundles/i18n, saved/AI-translated strings were shadowed → "Save" appeared to do nothing on reload. GetI18nLocale now reads builder/i18n (overrides) first. AssetVersion unchanged (server-side fix). Carries v1.7.37 Content-Slider editor fix.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.37 (20260701) — ⭐FIX Content Slider editor regression: the packaged wwwroot shipped a STALE content-slider widget plugin (js/plugins/megaform-widget-content-slider.js, old 20KB from 06-17) instead of the 06-28 redesign (42KB, Overlay/Card/Cards templates + Ken Burns + drag-follow) → installing overwrote the live plugin with the old one → the rich "Open Slider Designer" modal was missing. Rebuilt the plugin from source (tsc plugins/tsconfig) and synced to the package wwwroot. AssetVersion→20260701-B341. Carries v1.7.36 Import-JSON fix.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.36 (20260701) — ⭐FIX Wizard Import-JSON: (1) the DEPLOYED default templates put customHtml/customCss at the TOP LEVEL (not inside settings) → wizardTemplateFromJson now merges top-level custom* into settings so premium templates import WITH their shell (was silently downgraded to a plain standard form). (2) Import was silent (a valid file only changed the off-screen name field → felt like nothing happened) → now shows a toast "Imported \"…\" — N fields loaded", and JSON/parse errors surface as toasts instead of alert(). +4 wiz.import_* keys (de/vi). AssetVersion→20260701-B340. Carries v1.7.35 Wizard i18n.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.35 (20260701) — ⭐Form Wizard i18n: the wizard shell, step-nav, Setup step and Template-Gallery/Import-JSON modal are now keyed under wiz.* (46 keys) with German + Vietnamese translations shipped and English placeholders for the rest (fill via the in-product "Translate (AI)" tool). I18N_CACHE_VERSION bumped so stale locale caches drop. AssetVersion→20260701-B339. Carries v1.7.34.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.34 (20260701) — ⭐NEW option-icon PALETTE (pick emoji + MegaForm icon catalog for Chips/Cards option icons, no more raw typing) + FIX euro-youth stray 1px card border above the stepper (CustomShellCompatibilityCssService NOINNER now recognizes the nested .ey-card so the transparent outer .mfp stays borderless) + Form Wizard entry paths: a Template Gallery browse modal (category + search + preview) and Import-JSON, parallel to starting from scratch. Complete language packs (38 locales). AssetVersion→20260701-B338.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.33 (20260626) — ⭐FIX AI multi-step + AI form polish: (1) AI multi-step forms always showed an EMPTY first page — a page-break Section on the FIRST field made calculatePages() emit an empty leading page; it now only starts a new page when the current page has content (leading/consecutive page breaks no longer create blank pages). (2) Step labels are now derived from the actual page structure (fieldPages) — the leading section names step 1 correctly instead of a generic off-by-one "Step 1". (3) Multi-step (standard) forms dropped the gray --mf-page-bg wrapper frame ("card thừa bên ngoài") via .mf-form-wrapper:has(.mf-steps) so the white card sits on the page, consistent with the frameless single-page AI forms. (4) AI pure-grid (custom-shell) forms had ~36px DOUBLE field spacing (per-field margin-bottom STACKED on the container flex gap) — .mfp .mf-field-group margin-bottom:0 lets the shell gap own spacing (→16px). AssetVersion→20260626-B287. Includes v1.7.32 builder template-gallery regression fixes.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.32 (20260626) — ⭐FIX builder template-gallery regressions (Oqtane fullscreen): (1) "Template Preview" pane was BLANK — the loader's inline live-form suppressor (scan()) cloaked the in-memory preview .mf-form-wrapper because the preview modal is a body-level [data-mf-overlay] OUTSIDE the builder root; scan() now skips wrappers inside [data-mf-overlay]. (2) "Upload Template" file dialog didn't open for users on a stale cached builder.js — the loader's BUILDER_BUNDLE_VERSION was a HARDCODED constant ('20260626-B244') that never busted the cache when builder.js was rebuilt; it now derives from the loader's own ?v (= AssetVersion), so one AssetVersion bump busts loader + builder + builder CSS together. AssetVersion→20260626-B284. Includes v1.7.31 — ⭐COMPLETE LANGUAGE PACKS + drift guard. Fixed incomplete i18n in the package: js/plugins/i18n was stale (1189 keys) and top-level js/i18n was absent — both now carry the full canonical catalog (1268 keys × 18 locales), matching js/builder/i18n + js/bundles/i18n. Root cause: pack.cmd never ran the i18n platform-sync, so the wwwroot wildcard shipped partial packs. Fix is permanent: i18n-sync-platforms.cjs now covers all four Oqtane i18n dirs (auto-creating missing ones), and pack.cmd runs it + a verify-package-complete.cjs guard that ABORTS the pack if any i18n/KB directory is incomplete. KB (34 TemplateGuides .md + 8 PromptRecipes via wwwroot, ai-knowledge-seed.json + RazorWidgets embedded in the DLLs) and SQL (EF migrations in the Server DLL) verified complete. AssetVersion→20260626-B283. Carries v1.7.30 settings-popup trim + v1.7.29 i18n/popup. dropped the redundant subtitle line, the duplicate inner "Module form" label (the accordion header already says it), and the clean-state "Active preset: …" line (dupe of the header meta). AssetVersion→20260626-B282 (cache-bust). Builds on v1.7.29 — ⭐SETTINGS PANE: i18n + POPUP. The in-page ⚙ Settings UI (Module form / Theme &amp; Layout / Theme preset / Layout / Page integration) is now (1) fully localized — ~67 new vd.set.* keys wired through the runtime catalog with REAL translations for all 11 maintained locales + Vietnamese (was 100% hardcoded English), and (2) opens as a TRUE centered popup with a dim backdrop instead of an inline pane. Also closed the i18n drift gate: +12 missing subs.* "Send to Inbox" keys added + translated (gate back to PASS). Inherits v1.7.28 clean-host install fix (all MF_* tables created on a fresh host).</releaseNotes>
    <summary>Dynamic form builder module for Oqtane CMS</summary>

    <packageTypes>
      <!-- "Dependency" is the standard NuGet library type — confirmed working by CISS.SideMenu reference -->
      <packageType name="Dependency" />
      <!-- Oqtane.Framework: minimum compatible framework version — read by InstallationManager XPath -->
      <packageType name="Oqtane.Framework" version="6.1.2" />
    </packageTypes>

    <dependencies>
      <group targetFramework="net9.0" />
    </dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         COMPLETENESS (verified in v1.7.27): this package is COMPLETE for a clean Oqtane install —
         · DLLs: all MegaForm assemblies (Client/Server/Shared/Core/Sdk) + non-host deps
           (Newtonsoft.Json, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.Language, Microsoft.CodeAnalysis[.CSharp]),
           for BOTH net9.0 and net10.0 (entries below).
         · KBs / SQL scripts: the wwwroot wildcard ships all KB content under
           wwwroot\Modules\MegaForm\Resources\ (34 TemplateGuide .md + PromptRecipes) + all js/css/
           fonts/img. The MF_* table "SQL scripts" are the EF migrations COMPILED INTO the Server DLL
           (Migrations\*.cs + EntityBuilders) — not standalone files — so they ship inside lib\*.
         ⭐ For a COMPLETE build, run the full `pack.cmd` (it npm-builds the 7 JS bundles + Vite-syncs
            them into MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\wwwroot BEFORE packing). A lean re-pack only refreshes
            what's already in that wwwroot — stale/missing bundles there → an incomplete package.
         ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- net9.0 builds -->

    <!-- Client Blazor WASM DLL — tên chứa "Oqtane" → được load bởi IsOqtaneAssembly() -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net9.0" />

    <!-- Server DLL — tên chứa "Oqtane" → được load -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net9.0" />

    <!-- Shared DLL — tên chứa "Oqtane" → được load -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net9.0" />

    <!-- Core DLL — tên KHÔNG chứa "Oqtane" → KHÔNG được load vào AppDomain -->
    <!-- Nhưng vẫn cần trong bin/ vì Client/Server DLL có reference đến nó -->
    <!-- .NET runtime sẽ tự resolve khi cần (dependency resolution) -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Core.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />

    <!-- Third-party dependencies not provided by Oqtane host -->
    <!-- Newtonsoft.Json is used by MegaForm.Core; Oqtane 6 does NOT ship it -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\Newtonsoft.Json.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <!-- [pkg-fix 20260625] MegaForm runtime deps the Oqtane host does NOT provide. Without these a
         CLEAN-host install crashes at startup (ReflectionTypeLoadException during Oqtane's assembly
         scan): MegaForm.Sdk → Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.Language → Roslyn (CodeAnalysis). The
         :5070 dev site only worked because it had accumulated them from earlier manual deploys. -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Sdk.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.Language.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.CSharp.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />

    <!-- net10.0 builds (Oqtane 10.x hosts, e.g. :5070 Oqtane.MSSQL3 + :5000 Oqtane.New10) -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Core.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\Newtonsoft.Json.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Sdk.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.Language.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.CSharp.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />

    <!-- FIX 3: wwwroot — path đúng: wwwroot/Modules/MegaForm/** → deploy vào {webroot}/Modules/MegaForm/ -->
    <!-- Oqtane extract: bỏ 1 segment "wwwroot" → còn Modules/MegaForm/... → vào wwwroot/Modules/MegaForm/ -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\wwwroot\Modules\MegaForm\**\*.*" target="wwwroot\Modules\MegaForm" />

    <!-- Package metadata -->
    <file src="icon.png" target="" />
    <file src="license.txt" target="" />
    <!-- Note: license.lic under wwwroot\Modules\MegaForm\ is already packed by the
         wildcard above (**\*.*). Do NOT add an explicit entry here — NuGet will
         throw NU5050 (duplicate destination). -->
  </files>
</package>
